cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*BMarty Bergen: ^*N|cp||at|The one time when you don't want to make a takeout double, when that option is available, is when you have a 5-card major and a normal strength hand. You want to overcall with those hands in one of a major. That will be the best way to show partner you've got 5. If you make a takeout double, you can't show your 5-card major later, unless you have a big hand, because showing your major later would promise a big double.|
PG| ***** 5 ***** |


AT|

